President Obama held a meeting with college presidents and education thought leaders to discuss reducing college costs and improving quality. The participants included Dr. King Alexander, Dr. Francisco Cigarroa, Dr. Jared Cohon, Dr. Freeman Hrabowski, Dr. William "Brit" Kirwan, Dr. Robert Mendenhall, Dr. Larry Shinn, Mr. Thomas Snyder, Dr. Holden Thorp, Dr. Nancy Zimpher, Mr. Jamie Merisotis, and Ms. Jane Wellman. The meeting focused on the need for innovative solutions to make higher education more affordable and increase access for all Americans. The attendees shared their experiences in promoting innovation, reducing costs, and increasing productivity despite reduced funding at the state level.